Name: hh3cIKETunnelStart
Description:
This notification is generated when an IPsec Phase-1
IKE Tunnel is created.

Name: hh3cIKETunnelStop
Description:
This notification is generated when an IPsec Phase-1
IKE Tunnel is deleted.

Name: hh3cIKENoSaFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IKE tunnel
has a non-existent SA error.

Name: hh3cIKEEncryFailFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IKE tunnel
has an encrypting failure.

Name: hh3cIKEDecryFailFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IKE tunnel
has a decrypting failure.

Name: hh3cIKEInvalidProposalFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
invalid proposal occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEAuthFailFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
authentication failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEInvalidCookieFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
invalid cookie failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEAttrNotSuppFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1 unsupported
attribute failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEUnsportExchTypeFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
unsupported exchange type failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEInvalidIdFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
invalid id failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEInvalidProtocolFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the processing for
an IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel has a protocol related errors.

Name: hh3cIKECertTypeUnsuppFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
unsupported certificate type failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEInvalidCertAuthFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
invalid certificate authorization failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKElInvalidSignFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
invalid signature failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKECertUnavailableFailure
Description:
This notification is generated when the IPsec phase-1
certificate unavailable failure occurs.

Name: hh3cIKEProposalAdd
Description: This notification is generated when an IKE proposal is added.

Name: hh3cIKEProposalDel
Description: This notification is generated when an IKE proposal is deleted.
